## Architecture (clean-architecture slice, docs/architecture/02)

- **domain/** — aggregates, value objects, domain events, repository ports. Pure (`@platform/domain`).
- **application/** — use-cases + outbound port usage. Depends on domain + ports only.
- **infrastructure/** — adapters (persistence, outbox/messaging, external). Implements the ports.
- **interfaces/** — inbound boundary (controllers, event consumers).

Add building blocks with `pnpm gen aggregate` and `pnpm gen use-case`. Dependency direction
`domain ← application ← messaging ← infrastructure` is enforced by `pnpm arch`. See
`services/example` for a complete reference.

## Dependencies

`@platform/{domain, application, contracts, repository, types, utils}` (add `@platform/messaging` /
`@platform/domain-events` when the context emits or consumes integration events).

## Extension points

Wire the slice in a composition root and add a transport adapter at the interfaces boundary.
